--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Note: this case study requires GHC 7.8 to run.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

First install HERMIT version 1.0.0.0, which can be done via Cabal:

> cabal update
> cabal install hermit-1.0.0.0

Then install the package that contains the lemma library for the case study:

> cd hermit-century-lemmas
> cabal install

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The hermit-century-lemmas package can be tested by descending into the FoldrFusionExample directory and invoking
HERMIT as follows:

> hermit FoldrFusionExample.hs +FoldrFusionExample FoldrFusionExample.hec

HERMIT should report that the foldr-fusion lemma, and several subsidiary lemmas, have been successfully proven.

To get a feel for HERMIT, try running the example without loading the script:

> hermit FoldrFusionExample.hs +FoldrFusionExample

And then type in the commands from the HERMIT script "FoldrFusionExample.hec" one by one.  Note that lines starting
"--" are comments, not HERMIT commands.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To run the entire case study, invoke HERMIT in this directory as follows:

> hermit Century.hs Century.hec

If it runs successfully, you can use the HERMIT command "show-lemmas" to display all the lemmas (which should be
noted as proved).

hermit> show-lemmas

To get a feel for using HERMIT, try re-doing the proof of one of the lemmas.  E.g.

hermit> prove-lemma "6.8"

and then type in the commands from the HERMIT script "verify-6-8.hec" one by one.  Note that lines starting
"--" are comments, not HERMIT commands.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
